19:30.388 --> 19:32.055
Hey.

19:34.442 --> 19:37.227
What are you doing
out here, miss lily?

19:37.229 --> 19:40.029
Oh, let's get out of there.

19:40.031 --> 19:42.732
Oh, oh, okay.

19:42.734 --> 19:45.401
Hey.

19:45.403 --> 19:47.737
Aw.

19:51.993 --> 19:53.826
Nora: "researchers found
themselves intrigued

19:53.828 --> 19:56.129
By the anomalous phenomenon
of the departure cluster,

19:56.131 --> 19:59.249
The most extreme example of which is
the notorious Brandenburg carousel."

19:59.251 --> 20:01.084
They never confirmed
that fucking carousel.

20:01.086 --> 20:04.254
Some genius in German
tourism cooked it up.

20:04.256 --> 20:05.888
<i>[doorbell rings]</i>

20:13.181 --> 20:16.015
- Lily?
- She was on the hood of the truck.

20:16.017 --> 20:17.984
Oh, my God.

20:17.986 --> 20:20.903
