20:31.950 --> 20:35.084
My daughter Erin did that
same thing when she was four.

20:36.338 --> 20:39.122
Oh, I didn't know
you had another daughter.

20:39.124 --> 20:41.257
I used to, but she's gone now.

20:41.259 --> 20:43.092
My son, too.

20:45.630 --> 20:47.714
Oh, I'm so sorry.

20:47.716 --> 20:50.633
Well, thank you again.

20:57.976 --> 21:01.027
<i>[music playing]</i>

21:02.814 --> 21:04.897
Kevin: <i>Don't tell me
how to fucking do it.</i>

21:07.285 --> 21:09.485
I know how to strip fucking...

21:09.487 --> 21:11.738
<i>It's wallpaper.</i>

21:11.740 --> 21:15.124
Well, then don't fucking tell me.

21:15.126 --> 21:16.826
Who are you talking to?

21:19.381 --> 21:21.748
Myself.

21:21.750 --> 21:24.050
Oh, shit.

21:24.052 --> 21:26.252
I took her to the hardware store
and I had all that shit to carry

21:26.254 --> 21:28.888
And then I... I forgot to
go back out and get her.

21:28.890 --> 21:30.590
- I am so sorry.
- Kevin. Kevin.

21:30.592 --> 21:32.809
It's okay. It happens.

21:32.811 --> 21:34.177
It's okay.

21:36.398 --> 21:38.064
- I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

21:38.066 --> 21:40.316
I'm so sorry.

21:40.318 --> 21:41.934
You should hop in the shower.

21:41.936 --> 21:43.653
I'm gonna take Mary to visit Matt

21:43.655 --> 21:46.522
And then I'll meet you at the
visitors' center for the fundraiser.

21:46.524 --> 21:47.440
Yeah.

21:47.442 --> 21:48.941
- Wait, what?
- The fundraiser.

21:48.943 --> 21:51.027
For the Murphys
and the other missing girls.

21:51.029 --> 21:53.363
- We're going to that?
- Why wouldn't we?

21:53.365 --> 21:56.866
Because we asked them for help and
they fucking banished your brother.

21:56.868 --> 21:58.701
Matt banished himself.

21:58.703 --> 22:01.704
And people aren't at their best
when they're in that kind of pain.

22:01.706 --> 22:04.207
We should support them.
That's what neighbors do.

22:08.463 --> 22:11.631
- <i>[steam hisses]</i>
- Oh, shit. Fuck.

22:11.633 --> 22:14.517
- [hissing stops]
- Fuck.

22:22.060 --> 22:24.394
- Have you seen my batteries?
- Huh?

22:24.396 --> 22:25.978
The batteries for my ears.

22:25.980 --> 22:27.864
They're not in the kitchen drawer.

22:27.866 --> 22:29.982
You want me to run out
to the pharmacy?

22:29.984 --> 22:31.984
No, I have some upstairs.

22:33.571 --> 22:35.738
You think this is on me?

22:35.740 --> 22:36.823
What?

22:36.825 --> 22:39.459
People throwing rocks
through our window.

22:39.461 --> 22:43.296
You think it's because of what I do?

22:46.418 --> 22:50.303
That man that you beat
the shit out of this morning,

22:50.305 --> 22:52.388
He thinks it's because
he was selling our water.

22:52.390 --> 22:53.890
No, he was selling lies.

22:53.892 --> 22:57.009
Then why'd you take his palm print?

22:57.011 --> 23:00.012
Because I seem to recall
there being one left

23:00.014 --> 23:03.015
On the car that our daughter
disappeared from.

23:08.940 --> 23:10.440
Let's just call this what it is.

23:10.442 --> 23:12.942
What is it?

23:12.944 --> 23:16.362
You need to hit people because
you need to hit people.

23:34.299 --> 23:36.299
I'm trying.

23:43.942 --> 23:45.725
I know, babe.

23:58.957 --> 24:00.873
<i>[soft chatter]</i>

24:15.423 --> 24:18.007
SPF 75? What a joke.

24:18.009 --> 24:21.260
Anything over 30
is basically useless.

24:21.262 --> 24:22.478
<i>[door opens]</i>

24:23.431 --> 24:25.648
- Hey.
- Hey.

24:25.650 --> 24:27.066
We're going to visit Matt.

24:27.068 --> 24:29.352
Do you want to come to the fundraiser
with us or go with your dad?

24:29.354 --> 24:32.021
Actually, Michael asked me.

24:32.023 --> 24:34.156
How do his parents feel about that?

24:34.158 --> 24:37.193
I don't think that he asked them.

24:37.195 --> 24:40.830
And I'm not really asking you either.

24:42.116 --> 24:44.200
Well, if you were,
I'd say he's a sweet guy

24:44.202 --> 24:46.202
And I'm happy for you.

24:47.839 --> 24:49.789
Thanks.

24:50.842 --> 24:52.091
All right, I'll see you there?

24:52.093 --> 24:54.010
See you there.

24:54.012 --> 24:55.795
<i>[phone chiming]</i>

24:56.229 --> 24:57.856
_

25:00.468 --> 25:02.121
- Hello.
- Hebert: <i>Miss Durst,</i>

25:02.122 --> 25:04.804
<i>please don't hang up.
It's Allison Hebert again.</i>

25:04.806 --> 25:08.057
<i>If I could have one moment, please?</i>

25:08.059 --> 25:09.942
What do you want?

25:09.944 --> 25:12.645
<i>I need to apologize
for my colleague Dr. Cuarto.</i>

25:12.647 --> 25:17.066
<i>He's a great scientist,
but he lacks people skills.</i>

25:17.068 --> 25:18.618
<i>He should not have come to your home</i>

25:18.620 --> 25:20.486
<i>To collect the data from you
without permission.</i>

25:20.488 --> 25:23.456
- Data?
- <i>Yes.</i>

25:23.458 --> 25:27.410
<i>I must say the measurements he
took were very promising. Very.</i>

25:27.412 --> 25:30.212
<i>If you'd allow us, we could
guarantee their accuracy</i>

25:30.214 --> 25:32.915
<i>By replicating them
in laboratory conditions.</i>

25:34.419 --> 25:36.302
You think I'm a lens?

25:36.304 --> 25:38.254
<i>You're familiar with this theory?</i>

25:38.256 --> 25:40.890
Not really. I don't...

25:40.892 --> 25:42.308
I just read an article.

25:42.310 --> 25:44.810
<i>Miss Durst, you moved to Jarden,</i>

25:44.812 --> 25:46.929
<i>a town with no departures,</i>

25:46.931 --> 25:50.066
<i>And that very night
three girls disappeared,</i>

25:50.068 --> 25:53.436
<i>One of whom lived next door to you.</i>

25:53.438 --> 25:56.689
<i>Yes, we believe you are a lens.</i>

25:56.691 --> 26:00.109
Why? Do you know why me?

26:00.111 --> 26:03.279
<i>Well, this is where
our research is, um...</i>

26:03.281 --> 26:04.864
<i>Divisive.</i>

26:04.866 --> 26:08.034
<i>I would like very much
to discuss this in person.</i>

26:08.036 --> 26:10.169
Please just tell me.

26:10.171 --> 26:13.589
<i>Miss durst, we believe
that the demon Azrael</i>

26:13.591 --> 26:16.542
<i>has chosen you
as his earthbound instrument.</i>

26:16.544 --> 26:19.712
<i>This entity resides in you
through no fault of your own</i>

26:19.714 --> 26:22.465
<i>and is responsible for
the chaos that surrounds you</i>

26:22.467 --> 26:24.383
<i>and possibly many others.</i>

26:24.385 --> 26:26.469
<i>Dr. Cuarto and I have
contacted the Vatican...</i>

26:26.471 --> 26:28.137
[clicks]

26:28.139 --> 26:30.473
[laughing]

26:35.980 --> 26:37.947
[crying]

27:11.649 --> 27:13.683
<i>[high-pitched whine]</i>

27:16.070 --> 27:18.354
<i>[audio muted]</i>

27:27.582 --> 27:29.532
[muted] Hey!

27:32.370 --> 27:33.669
Hey!

28:01.232 --> 28:03.733
- [tires screech]
- [horn honks]

28:08.573 --> 28:11.707
- Why'd you run?
- I was just dropping off...

28:11.709 --> 28:15.461
Wait, wait, wait. Say it
again and say it slow.

28:15.463 --> 28:17.546
[muted speech]

28:17.548 --> 28:19.799
<i>[high-pitched whine]</i>

28:25.723 --> 28:28.808
<i>[faint music playing]</i>

28:30.928 --> 28:33.012
[humming]

28:34.682 --> 28:36.732
What the fuck is this?

28:40.605 --> 28:42.104
That's a pie.

28:42.106 --> 28:44.523
Why'd you send it to my house?

28:44.525 --> 28:47.493
Well, 'cause I know you're in pain.

28:47.495 --> 28:49.328
<i>John got a pie on his birthday.</i>

28:49.330 --> 28:51.447
<i>We weren't in pain then.</i>

28:51.449 --> 28:53.449
You weren't?

28:56.120 --> 28:58.838
Is this about Michael
coming to pray with me?

29:00.541 --> 29:02.091
What?

29:02.093 --> 29:04.426
Oh, he didn't tell you.

29:07.131 --> 29:09.181
I'm not gonna say this again.

29:09.183 --> 29:11.300
Stay away from my family.

29:13.304 --> 29:15.271
I know what I did.

29:15.273 --> 29:17.723
And I know I can never make it right.

29:19.193 --> 29:21.360
And I also know that
you wish it wasn't so,

29:21.362 --> 29:25.648
But I am your family, Erika.

29:32.073 --> 29:34.740
You want to take a bird with you?

29:37.995 --> 29:40.129
Why the fuck would I do that?

29:52.093 --> 29:54.343
[engine starts]

29:56.647 --> 29:59.098
<i>[chatter]</i>

30:05.690 --> 30:07.773
<i>[drums playing]</i>

30:09.694 --> 30:11.110
Hey.

30:12.079 --> 30:13.746
<i>I come bearing gifts.</i>

30:13.748 --> 30:15.331
Hey!

30:24.175 --> 30:26.375
- Thanks.
- Yummy.

30:27.962 --> 30:29.595
- Hey.
- Hey.

30:29.597 --> 30:32.631
- That was for you.
- No, we share everything here.

30:32.633 --> 30:33.766
Hup.

30:33.768 --> 30:36.051
Hello, my love.

30:36.053 --> 30:39.021
I'm sorry you have
to come out here again.

30:39.023 --> 30:42.441
Not all the people are degenerates.

30:42.443 --> 30:44.526
So this is, what,
your new congregation?

30:44.528 --> 30:48.864
Nah, just a bunch of folks
who needed a little guidance.

30:48.866 --> 30:51.066
And all you had to do to win their respect
was humiliate yourself in the stocks.

30:51.068 --> 30:56.238
No, all I had to do was refuse to
let someone else take my place.

30:56.240 --> 30:58.240
Suffering breeds compassion.

30:59.794 --> 31:01.493
Nobody does it like you, Matt.

31:01.495 --> 31:02.795
<i>[chuckles]</i>

31:02.797 --> 31:04.163
Matt: <i>You clean the tube every night?</i>

31:04.165 --> 31:06.715
Of course. And we got the bed
like you had back in Mapleton.

31:06.717 --> 31:09.418
They're expensive. You and
Kevin didn't have to do that.

31:09.420 --> 31:11.387
It's fine. We rented it.

31:11.389 --> 31:14.056
The OB appointment is this Friday,

31:14.058 --> 31:16.675
So we'll pick you up
on the way out of town.

31:16.677 --> 31:19.094
I bet you're looking
forward to that, huh?

31:20.681 --> 31:22.481
Get our first peek.

31:22.483 --> 31:24.516
Hear the heartbeat.

31:26.237 --> 31:28.153
Any sign of her...

31:28.155 --> 31:30.406
Waking up?

31:30.408 --> 31:31.991
No, Matt.

31:33.160 --> 31:35.160
Give her time.

31:38.916 --> 31:40.199
You look nice.

31:40.201 --> 31:41.700
Going somewhere special?

31:41.702 --> 31:43.168
Oh, we're going to the fundraiser

31:43.170 --> 31:45.170
for the families
of the missing girls.

31:45.172 --> 31:47.423
They need money to
continue the search, so...

31:50.344 --> 31:51.794
What?

31:51.796 --> 31:54.046
You bringing Mary?

31:54.048 --> 31:56.015
<i>Yeah, we're going straight from here.</i>

31:56.017 --> 31:57.516
Hmm.

31:57.518 --> 31:59.885
What, Matt?

31:59.887 --> 32:03.305
The Murphys don't believe what
happened to her. They deny it.

32:03.307 --> 32:06.809
You bringing her to their party
may be regarded as hostile.

32:06.811 --> 32:09.061
They lost their daughter.

32:09.063 --> 32:11.613
Why would I feel
hostile towards them?

32:11.615 --> 32:13.899
I don't know. Why would you?

32:15.536 --> 32:17.319
Fuck you, Matt.

32:23.995 --> 32:26.795
<i>♪ Don't let me change ♪</i>

32:28.632 --> 32:31.383
<i>♪ Don't rearrange me ♪</i>

32:31.385 --> 32:36.171
<i>♪ Don't ever let me come down ♪</i>

32:36.173 --> 32:39.975
<i>♪ Don't let my feet
touch on the ground... ♪</i>

32:39.977 --> 32:42.011
- Let me help you with that.
- I got it.

32:42.013 --> 32:43.762
Thank you.

32:49.437 --> 32:51.820
She loved that on you.

32:54.658 --> 32:56.658
<i>I think she just wanted
you to give it to her,</i>

32:56.660 --> 32:59.661
<i>but you never took the hint.</i>

32:59.663 --> 33:01.613
I took the hint.

33:01.615 --> 33:04.199
Just wanted it for myself.

33:11.709 --> 33:13.292
Michael.

33:13.294 --> 33:15.044
<i>I'm in here.</i>

33:20.434 --> 33:23.268
- You gonna get dressed?
- Yeah, just a minute.

33:30.694 --> 33:33.312
[sighs]

33:33.314 --> 33:35.781
I know you go out there
to pray with him.

33:37.451 --> 33:39.451
Who?

33:39.453 --> 33:42.237
Don't make me say his name.

33:42.239 --> 33:44.490
Do you know what your father
would do if he found out?

33:44.492 --> 33:45.874
Shoot him again?

33:49.630 --> 33:52.081
Michael, you can't
go out there anymore.

33:52.083 --> 33:55.467
- He deserves forgiveness.
- No, not him.

33:55.469 --> 33:59.138
Everyone who asks for it
deserves it, Mom.

33:59.140 --> 34:01.006
Even him.

34:04.845 --> 34:06.762
Michael, go get dressed.

34:28.002 --> 34:29.668
But again, thank you.

34:29.670 --> 34:31.753
[quiet chatter]

34:37.594 --> 34:39.628
<i>[phone chiming]</i>

34:44.685 --> 34:46.601
Listen to me, if you call
this number again,

34:46.603 --> 34:48.137
I will report you
to the fucking police.

34:48.139 --> 34:50.139
Do you understand me?

34:50.141 --> 34:51.889
Laurie: <i>Is this Nora?</i>

34:51.891 --> 34:54.193
Who is this?

34:54.195 --> 34:56.277
<i>It's Laurie Garvey.</i>

35:04.288 --> 35:06.238
Nora, are you there?

35:07.825 --> 35:09.658
How did you get this number?

35:09.660 --> 35:11.376
<i>On the internet.</i>

35:11.378 --> 35:14.663
It's really easy to unlist
if you want.

35:17.001 --> 35:19.334
<i>I'm sorry to call you.
I know it's not fair,</i>

35:19.336 --> 35:22.588
But I just need to know,
is Tom there?

35:22.590 --> 35:24.840
- <i>Tom?</i>
- My son, Tommy.

35:24.842 --> 35:27.342
Is he there with you in Texas?

35:30.181 --> 35:32.981
No, he's not here.
I've never even met him.

35:32.983 --> 35:34.983
Is something wrong?

35:38.189 --> 35:40.405
Well, if you do see him,
if he comes there,

35:40.407 --> 35:44.359
will you tell him
that I'm worried about him?

35:45.946 --> 35:48.530
Can you tell him I'm sorry?

35:50.251 --> 35:52.534
Okay, I'll do that.

35:54.705 --> 35:56.538
All right. Thanks, Nora.

35:57.541 --> 35:59.091
Good-bye.

36:00.594 --> 36:02.211
Bye.

36:17.695 --> 36:19.444
Hey, how was Matt?

36:19.446 --> 36:21.313
Fine.

36:21.315 --> 36:23.815
- You okay?
- Yeah, let's go sit.

36:23.817 --> 36:25.400
Woman: <i>Hi there.</i>

36:25.402 --> 36:27.569
We're taking donations
for the reward fund

36:27.571 --> 36:30.405
and for the families to hire
out-of-state resources for the search.

36:30.407 --> 36:32.908
Oh, yes, of course.
We'd like to give 500, please.

36:32.910 --> 36:35.494
<i>That's very generous.
Do you have a Paypal account?</i>

36:35.496 --> 36:37.579
- Sorry?
- A Paypal account.

36:37.581 --> 36:38.914
That's how we do the donations.

36:38.916 --> 36:41.500
If you don't have one,
I can set one up for you.

36:41.502 --> 36:45.003
- No, I have one.
- Then you know the drill.

36:45.005 --> 36:47.506
<i>There you go.</i>

36:47.508 --> 36:49.558
<i>[faint music playing]</i>

36:52.263 --> 36:55.097
Let's grab those seats up there.

36:55.099 --> 36:56.765
Sure.

36:56.767 --> 36:58.483
Excuse me.

37:00.271 --> 37:02.938
- Evening.
- Oh, hey there.

37:02.940 --> 37:05.407
Oh, Kevin, this is...

37:05.409 --> 37:07.276
I'm sorry, I forgot your name.

37:07.278 --> 37:08.744
George Brevity, DSD.

37:08.746 --> 37:10.829
Oh, did you guys work together or...?

37:10.831 --> 37:11.947
Mm-mmm.

37:11.949 --> 37:14.116
I sent you that article.
Did you get it?

37:14.118 --> 37:16.451
- Yeah, it was horseshit.
- <i>Really?</i>

37:16.453 --> 37:19.121
Our research guys thought there was
some pretty interesting stuff there.

37:19.123 --> 37:21.456
They're working some of that
data into the new questionnaire.

37:23.443 --> 37:25.844
<i>Okay, if everybody could
just take their seats.</i>

37:25.846 --> 37:27.546
- Excuse me. I've got to record this.
- Okay.

37:27.548 --> 37:29.298
<i>We're gonna go ahead and get started.</i>

37:29.300 --> 37:30.849
<i>Thank you.</i>

37:30.851 --> 37:32.968
<i>[mic feedback squealing]</i>

37:40.060 --> 37:42.944
♪ But in Jarden town
the sun shone bright ♪

37:42.946 --> 37:45.530
♪ A miracle ♪

37:45.532 --> 37:48.033
<i>♪ The light above bore down ♪</i>

37:48.035 --> 37:51.153
<i>♪ It's a miracle ♪</i>

37:51.155 --> 37:53.989
<i>♪ Our hearts are pure,
we knew for sure ♪</i>

37:53.991 --> 37:56.291
<i>♪ A miracle ♪</i>

37:56.293 --> 38:02.581
<i>♪ That God has spared our town ♪</i>

38:02.583 --> 38:05.300
[applause]

38:08.255 --> 38:12.090
Emily: <i>On behalf of me
and Sam and Loretta</i>

38:12.092 --> 38:14.176
And John and Erika,

38:14.178 --> 38:16.728
We are so grateful

38:16.730 --> 38:18.730
for y'all coming out
to support our girls

38:18.732 --> 38:22.317
so we can get them back to that
beautiful choir real soon.

38:22.319 --> 38:26.855
<i>If Taylor and Violet
and Evie are out there,</i>

38:26.857 --> 38:29.358
<i>we're gonna find them.</i>

38:34.198 --> 38:37.783
Our girls were such good friends
ever since they were little.

38:37.785 --> 38:40.535
<i>Emily and I put together
this little slide show.</i>

38:40.537 --> 38:43.338
<i>I hope you enjoy it.</i>

38:43.340 --> 38:45.540
<i>[music playing]</i>

38:52.349 --> 38:55.634
<i>♪ All along there was a fever ♪</i>

38:59.890 --> 39:04.276
<i>♪ A cold sweat,
hotheaded believer ♪</i>

39:08.065 --> 39:10.782
<i>♪ I threw my hands in the air ♪</i>

39:10.784 --> 39:13.368
<i>♪ Said show me something ♪</i>

39:16.623 --> 39:21.743
<i>♪ He said, "if you dare,
come a little closer" ♪</i>

39:25.883 --> 39:31.386
<i>♪ Round and around
and around and around we go ♪</i>

39:33.757 --> 39:36.558
<i>♪ Oh, now tell me now ♪</i>

39:36.560 --> 39:40.145
<i>♪ Tell me now,
tell me now you know ♪</i>

39:43.567 --> 39:47.269
<i>♪ Not really sure
how to feel about it ♪</i>

39:47.271 --> 39:51.606
<i>♪ Something in the way you move ♪</i>

39:51.608 --> 39:54.910
<i>♪ Makes me feel like I can't
live without you... ♪</i>

39:54.912 --> 39:56.695
- <i>[door opens]</i>
- <i>[goat bleating]</i>

39:56.697 --> 39:59.498
[bleating]

40:00.534 --> 40:04.169
Uh-uh. Uh-uh, no.

40:04.171 --> 40:06.455
<i>No.</i>

40:06.457 --> 40:09.341
No. How do I stop this?

40:09.343 --> 40:11.626
- <i>[music stops]</i>
- Jerry, uh-uh, no.

40:11.628 --> 40:13.512
You got to get out of here.

40:13.514 --> 40:15.130
[crowd murmuring]

40:15.132 --> 40:16.465
- Woman: <i>Let him do it.</i>
- No, Jerry.

40:16.467 --> 40:17.632
Come on, let him do it.

40:17.634 --> 40:19.217
He's trying to help.

40:19.219 --> 40:22.771
He's trying to help?
This man is crazy.

40:23.807 --> 40:26.224
He killed a goat on October 14

40:26.226 --> 40:28.143
Before any of us knew what happened

40:28.145 --> 40:30.979
<i>and he was locked up in jail
where he should have stayed.</i>

40:30.981 --> 40:34.983
But then all y'all decided
that Jerry must have saved us,

40:34.985 --> 40:36.651
that Jerry knew something.

40:36.653 --> 40:40.572
He sacrificed something
to protect us.

40:40.574 --> 40:43.575
<i>So now he's a holy man and
he gets to walk around here</i>

40:43.577 --> 40:46.995
Killing goats whenever he
feels like it just in case?

40:46.997 --> 40:48.797
John: <i>Babe, can you
calm down, please?</i>

40:48.799 --> 40:51.166
No, you let him do it, too.

40:51.168 --> 40:53.051
If there aren't
any miracles in Miracle,

40:53.053 --> 40:55.804
then why does he get a pass?

40:58.141 --> 41:02.594
Cecilia, you were trying on your
wedding dress when it happened, huh?

41:02.596 --> 41:05.063
So now you put it on every day

41:05.065 --> 41:07.265
and you take pictures
with the tourists, huh?

41:07.267 --> 41:09.651
Number 13 on the audio tour.

41:09.653 --> 41:11.903
Well, maybe you were
the one that saved us.

41:11.905 --> 41:13.522
Maybe, huh?

41:13.524 --> 41:17.526
We are the 9,261

41:17.528 --> 41:20.495
and we are spared.

41:20.497 --> 41:22.531
We're spared.

41:22.533 --> 41:25.417
<i>We're not spared.</i>

41:25.419 --> 41:27.669
We're not safe.

41:27.671 --> 41:30.622
All this shit we're walking around
here doing, it doesn't matter.

41:30.624 --> 41:34.125
It doesn't work. My daughter is gone.

41:34.127 --> 41:36.878
So no. No, Jerry.

41:36.880 --> 41:38.346
<i>She departed.</i>

41:47.975 --> 41:50.025
<i>[doors slam]</i>

41:57.951 --> 41:59.618
See you at home.

42:00.571 --> 42:02.237
Where are you going?

42:02.239 --> 42:05.657
Man: <i>Okay, folks,
everybody just stay seated.</i>

42:05.659 --> 42:08.076
<i>Everything's gonna be fine.</i>

42:09.630 --> 42:12.380
[knocks]

42:25.145 --> 42:27.596
- Hi.
- Hi.

42:29.683 --> 42:32.100
I was at the fundraiser.
Are you okay?

42:32.102 --> 42:33.935
I'm fine.

42:33.937 --> 42:35.654
Here.

42:35.656 --> 42:38.773
It's the questions
the DSD wants to ask you.

42:38.775 --> 42:40.575
Where did you get it?

42:40.577 --> 42:41.943
I borrowed it.

42:43.447 --> 42:46.114
That man, the agent isn't
going to leave you alone.

42:46.116 --> 42:49.200
I wanted you to have it so you could
see there's nothing to be scared of.

42:50.621 --> 42:52.003
I'm scared?

42:52.005 --> 42:53.338
Yes.

42:53.340 --> 42:55.373
Of what?

42:58.428 --> 43:00.462
You're scared that if you
answer these questions,

43:00.464 --> 43:03.298
everyone's gonna know that
your daughter didn't depart.

43:04.718 --> 43:06.267
She didn't?

43:11.975 --> 43:13.975
And those questions will prove it?

43:20.200 --> 43:22.784
Well, come on in and ask them.

43:38.969 --> 43:41.886
Did the missing person bite
or chew his or her fingernails?

43:41.888 --> 43:43.471
No.

43:43.473 --> 43:46.558
Did the missing person recently
commence new dietary habits

43:46.560 --> 43:48.677
including but not
restricted to vegan,

43:48.679 --> 43:50.345
gluten-free or paleolithic?

43:50.347 --> 43:51.713
No.

43:51.715 --> 43:54.466
Would you describe the
missing person as generous?

43:54.468 --> 43:55.667
Yes.

43:55.669 --> 43:58.003
Would you describe
yourself as generous?

43:58.005 --> 44:01.723
Generous people don't describe
themselves as generous.

44:01.725 --> 44:03.725
So no?

44:04.678 --> 44:07.012
No.

44:07.014 --> 44:08.847
To your knowledge,
did the missing person

44:08.849 --> 44:11.483
consume one or more alcoholic
beverages per day?

44:11.485 --> 44:12.851
No.

44:12.853 --> 44:15.520
Do you consume one or more
alcoholic beverages per day?

44:15.522 --> 44:16.905
No.

44:16.907 --> 44:19.774
Did the missing person use
aluminum-based antiperspirant?

44:19.776 --> 44:21.609
She uses secret.

44:22.863 --> 44:24.195
It's aluminum-based.

44:24.197 --> 44:26.865
Is the missing person
a product of a multiple birth?

44:26.867 --> 44:30.001
Yes, Evie and Michael are twins.

44:31.204 --> 44:33.004
Did the missing person
have visual impairment

44:33.006 --> 44:35.340
or wear corrective... lenses?

44:36.376 --> 44:38.009
Yes.

44:39.963 --> 44:43.048
Was the missing person diagnosed
with any neurological conditions

44:43.050 --> 44:45.016
Such as essential tremor,
Tourette's syndrome

44:45.018 --> 44:47.385
or any disorder
that manifested seizures?

44:48.889 --> 44:50.688
She has epilepsy.

44:51.975 --> 44:55.193
She had a seizure
the night she disappeared.

44:55.195 --> 44:57.228
You were there.

44:57.230 --> 44:59.114
Yeah, I remember.

44:59.116 --> 45:02.117
How often on average did you
dream about the missing person

45:02.119 --> 45:04.652
prior to their disappearance?

45:04.654 --> 45:06.237
<i>I don't know.</i>

45:06.239 --> 45:08.990
<i>Three or four times a month.</i>

45:08.992 --> 45:12.077
How often on average
do you dream about them now?

45:15.916 --> 45:17.549
Every night.

45:20.387 --> 45:22.220
To the best of your recollection,

45:22.222 --> 45:25.256
what were the last words the
missing person spoke to you?

45:27.761 --> 45:30.428
[sighs]

45:30.430 --> 45:32.430
I don't remember.

45:32.432 --> 45:34.566
You don't remember?

45:34.568 --> 45:36.935
No.

45:43.443 --> 45:45.443
To the best of your knowledge,
did the missing person

45:45.445 --> 45:48.530
ever express a desire to hurt
him or herself? If so, why?

45:48.532 --> 45:50.115
Absolutely not.

45:50.117 --> 45:53.118
Have you ever expressed a desire
to hurt yourself? If so, why?

45:53.120 --> 45:54.586
No.

45:54.588 --> 45:57.338
To the best of your knowledge,
did the missing person

45:57.340 --> 45:59.541
withdraw more than $1,000
from his or her bank

45:59.543 --> 46:02.343
within 30 days prior to their
disappearance? If so, what for?

46:02.345 --> 46:05.930
Evie's account is connected to ours.

46:05.932 --> 46:07.966
She didn't withdraw any money.

46:07.968 --> 46:10.768
Did you withdraw more than
$1,000 from your bank

46:10.770 --> 46:12.412
within 30 days prior
to the disappearance?

46:12.413 --> 46:13.855
If so, what for?

46:16.810 --> 46:18.643
Yes.

46:20.230 --> 46:22.147
If so, what for?

46:24.367 --> 46:26.651
<i>[clock ticking faintly]</i>

46:29.990 --> 46:32.490
I was gonna leave John.

46:39.833 --> 46:46.337
You're surprised
because we seem so happy.

46:52.179 --> 46:54.846
<i>My Grandmother was born here.</i>

46:54.848 --> 46:58.016
She lived here all her life.

46:58.018 --> 47:01.803
She used to tell us kids
this place is chosen.

47:01.804 --> 47:05.490
The Good Lord pointed His finger
down on the final day of creation

47:05.492 --> 47:08.660
And said: "You. The Jarden of Eden."

47:11.414 --> 47:13.248
We didn't believe her,

47:13.250 --> 47:16.417
but she said there was
a way to prove it,

47:16.419 --> 47:20.538
<i>a way to make your wishes come true.</i>

47:20.540 --> 47:22.874
<i>You take a bird,</i>

47:22.876 --> 47:25.593
you put it in a box and you bury it.

47:25.595 --> 47:28.546
Anywhere in the woods is fine.

47:28.548 --> 47:31.099
And you wait.

47:31.101 --> 47:33.384
You wait three days, you come back,

47:33.386 --> 47:36.721
dig it up, and if it's alive,

47:36.723 --> 47:40.225
right then is when
you make your wish.

47:40.227 --> 47:42.694
Little girls believe
all sorts of things,

47:42.696 --> 47:46.064
but I knew pretend when I heard it.

47:46.066 --> 47:51.035
Birds living in the ground
for three days is pretend.

47:51.037 --> 47:54.872
Making wishes is pretend.

47:57.577 --> 48:00.628
The Good Lord is pretend.

48:05.135 --> 48:07.919
And then on October 14,

48:07.921 --> 48:11.089
people went away from
everywhere except here.

48:12.425 --> 48:14.592
That was real.

48:14.594 --> 48:16.894
That happened.

48:18.181 --> 48:20.848
My Grandma had been
dead for 10 years,

48:20.850 --> 48:23.601
but she was right.

48:23.603 --> 48:25.603
This place was chosen.

48:29.359 --> 48:31.442
And about a month ago,

48:31.444 --> 48:34.329
I was walking out to my car and...

48:34.331 --> 48:35.997
I saw it.

48:37.200 --> 48:42.086
A sparrow right
by the driver's side door

48:42.088 --> 48:46.457
lying there like it was trying
to get me to help it.

48:46.459 --> 48:49.427
It was dehydrated.

48:49.429 --> 48:51.629
Almost dead.

48:54.184 --> 48:57.185
You think I nursed it
back to health, Nora?

49:00.807 --> 49:02.640
Depending on the size of the box,

49:02.642 --> 49:07.061
a bird can survive 20 hours.

49:07.063 --> 49:10.448
Anything over 30 hours
is medically impossible.

49:10.450 --> 49:13.368
And like I said, this bird,

49:13.370 --> 49:16.788
it didn't have anything left.

49:16.790 --> 49:19.874
So I waited the three days.

49:19.876 --> 49:22.827
I jogged out to the woods,

49:22.829 --> 49:25.580
I dug up the box,

49:25.582 --> 49:28.833
and I made my wish
before I opened it.

49:31.004 --> 49:35.139
I wished that my kids
would be okay if I left.

49:35.141 --> 49:38.976
Because they had no idea
I needed to go.

49:38.978 --> 49:41.896
No idea what it's like to pretend.

49:44.734 --> 49:48.686
Michael, he has his faith.

49:48.688 --> 49:51.489
He'd be fine.

49:51.491 --> 49:53.691
But Evie...

49:55.362 --> 49:58.279
She wouldn't understand.

49:58.281 --> 50:00.114
It would break her heart.

50:01.868 --> 50:05.086
So I wished that
she'd be okay without me.

50:10.377 --> 50:13.211
I opened up the box,

50:13.213 --> 50:15.213
the bird flew out.

50:18.184 --> 50:21.219
And the next night
my daughter was gone.

50:30.230 --> 50:32.563
Well, Erika, that's just...

50:34.401 --> 50:36.868
That's quite a stretch.

50:37.821 --> 50:39.987
<i>Your logic, I'm sorry,</i>

50:39.989 --> 50:42.874
<i>it's a little all over the place,
don't you think?</i>

50:44.794 --> 50:47.745
Well, what do you think?

50:47.747 --> 50:49.997
You wanted to leave your husband.

50:49.999 --> 50:53.167
Okay, so why didn't he go?
Why didn't you?

50:53.169 --> 50:55.920
140 million people
disappeared three years ago.

50:55.922 --> 50:57.255
Did you wish them away, too?

50:57.257 --> 50:58.890
Because that's a lot
of birds to bury, Erika.

50:58.892 --> 51:01.225
That's a flock of epic proportions.

51:03.897 --> 51:05.763
I get it. I felt the same as you.

51:05.765 --> 51:08.566
I... [sighs]

51:09.769 --> 51:12.236
I felt responsible
for losing my children.

51:12.238 --> 51:14.322
I thought it was my fault.

51:15.942 --> 51:19.277
But I moved past it.

51:19.279 --> 51:21.028
I evolved.

51:22.916 --> 51:25.333
Because that's pathetic.

51:29.255 --> 51:32.840
Terrible things happen in this world.

51:32.842 --> 51:37.545
And the only comfort we get
is that we didn't cause them.

51:37.547 --> 51:40.131
So I'm sorry, but...

51:40.133 --> 51:42.767
Erika, this had nothing
to do with you.

51:55.198 --> 51:58.032
Did they depart or did they die?

51:58.034 --> 52:00.535
What?

52:00.537 --> 52:03.371
Your children.

52:03.373 --> 52:06.073
You said you lost them.

52:06.075 --> 52:08.326
Did they depart

52:08.328 --> 52:10.878
or did they die?

52:15.802 --> 52:17.835
They departed.

52:19.672 --> 52:23.891
What were the last words
they said to you,

52:23.893 --> 52:26.260
to the best of your recollection?

52:44.330 --> 52:46.531
<i>[papers shuffle]</i>

52:56.092 --> 52:58.292
<i>[door opens]</i>

52:59.512 --> 53:01.212
<i>[door closes]</i>

53:08.721 --> 53:10.054
[sniffling]

53:10.056 --> 53:12.106
- Hey.
- Hey.

53:12.108 --> 53:13.858
Mary's asleep.

53:13.860 --> 53:15.359
Jill's putting the baby
down upstairs.

53:15.361 --> 53:17.194
Okay, I'll go up and help out.

53:17.196 --> 53:19.063
We need to talk.

53:21.568 --> 53:23.701
Can we do this tomorrow?

53:23.703 --> 53:26.153
It's important.

53:27.290 --> 53:30.575
Yes, honey, I know it's important,

53:30.577 --> 53:31.993
but can we just...

53:31.995 --> 53:34.245
I need to talk to you now, Nora.

53:44.173 --> 53:46.474
Have you been noticing
that I've been...

53:49.012 --> 53:51.262
kind of losing my mind?

53:51.264 --> 53:53.397
What?

53:56.686 --> 53:58.352
I'm letting you handcuff me
to the bed every night

53:58.354 --> 54:00.938
And we're acting like
that's totally normal.

54:03.443 --> 54:07.278
I left the baby... I forgot the baby

54:07.280 --> 54:09.947
and you act like that's no big deal.

54:09.949 --> 54:11.916
You had your hands full. It happens.

54:11.918 --> 54:13.367
I'm seeing someone.

54:15.421 --> 54:16.787
What?

54:16.789 --> 54:20.841
Um, I've been...

54:20.843 --> 54:22.793
Seeing someone.

54:26.633 --> 54:28.633
Who?

54:30.436 --> 54:32.937
Patti Levin.

54:34.857 --> 54:38.643
She ran the Guilty Remnant
in Mapleton.

54:50.373 --> 54:52.323
But she's dead.

54:57.797 --> 55:01.882
It started happening
right after we found Lily

55:01.884 --> 55:03.718
when you moved in.

55:05.054 --> 55:07.254
I thought she'd go away
when we came here.

55:10.510 --> 55:12.226
She didn't.

55:19.185 --> 55:21.519
Are you seeing her right now?

55:24.357 --> 55:26.941
Yeah.

55:26.943 --> 55:28.943
<i>Is she talking to you?</i>

55:31.247 --> 55:33.614
Yeah.

55:36.836 --> 55:39.120
What's she saying?

55:40.506 --> 55:42.089
<i>She's saying...</i>

55:44.794 --> 55:48.879
<i>She's saying I never should
have told you about her.</i>

55:52.719 --> 55:54.852
And...

55:59.726 --> 56:02.693
That I just made a big mistake.

56:02.695 --> 56:04.945
[shatters]

56:06.232 --> 56:08.449
<i>[distant dog barking]</i>

56:18.000 --> 56:21.000
<b>www.addic7ed.com</b>

56:22.746 --> 56:24.149
<i>[music playing]</i>

56:24.150 --> 56:26.417
<i>♪ A winter's day ♪</i>

56:28.654 --> 56:32.690
<i>♪ In a deep and dark December ♪</i>

56:36.929 --> 56:41.532
<i>♪ I am alone ♪</i>

56:41.534 --> 56:45.202
<i>♪ Gazing from my window
to the streets below ♪</i>

56:45.204 --> 56:49.106
<i>♪ On a freshly fallen
silent shroud of snow ♪</i>

56:49.108 --> 56:51.108
<i>♪ I am a rock ♪</i>

56:51.110 --> 56:55.312
<i>♪ I am an island ♪</i>

56:58.050 --> 57:01.352
<i>♪ And a rock feels no pain ♪</i>

57:01.354 --> 57:05.956
<i>♪ And an island never cries. ♪</i>

